{
  "answer": "**San Hyan Kamahayanikan** contains several explicit catalogues of named divine figures, including past Buddhas (Vipaśyin, Viśvabhū, Krakucchanda, Kanakamuni, Kāśyapa), future Buddhas (Ārya Maitreya up to Samantabhadra), and present Buddha (Śrī Śākyamuni); the four goddesses in Vairocana's retinue (Satvavajrī, Ratnavajrī, Dharmavajrī, Karmavajrī); and the four primary goddesses (Locanā, Pāṇḍaravāsinī, Māmakī, Tārā), alongside the Pañcatathāgata (Vairocana, Akṣobhya, Ratnasambhava, Amitābha, Amoghasiddhi).[^1][^2][^3][^4]\n\n**Slokantara** catalogues the four sister-goddesses of Rudra (Umā, Gaṅgā, Gaurī, Durgā), emulated by the *kṛṣṇa-brahmacārī*; and the eight Cāṇḍālas (seller of lime, seller of palm-wine, seller of indigo, launderer, potter, butcher, goldsmith, dyer), with a variant list of five (palm-wine tapper, launderer, butcher, potter, goldsmith).[^5][^6]\n\n**San Hyan Tattvajnana** features extensive lists of deities (Brahmā, Viṣṇu, Īśvara, Pañcaṛṣi, Saptaṛṣi, Devaṛṣi, Indra, Yama, Varuṇa, Kubera, Vaiśravaṇa, Vidyādhara, Gandharva, Dānava, Daitya, Rākṣasa, Bhūta, Yakṣa, Bhūta Dĕṅĕn, Bhūtakāla, Bhūtapiśāca); catalogues of *yoni*s for *buddhi-sattva* (Tripuruṣa, Pañcaṛṣi [Kuśika, Garga, Maitrī, Kuruṣya, Pṛtañjala], Saptaṛṣi, Devaṛṣi); for *buddhi-rajas* (Dānava, Daitya, Rākṣasa); and for *buddhi-tamas* (Bhūta Yakṣa, Bhūta Dĕṅĕn, Bhūta Kāla, Bhūta Piśāca), with descent chains (e.g., Tripuruṣa → Pañcaṛṣi → Saptaṛṣi → ... → Bhūta Piśāca → human → *triyak*).[^7][^8][^9]\n\nNo other works in the corpus contain such explicit lists or catalogues of named figures (e.g., Nāradasmṛti lists marriage forms and defects; Yājñavalkya Smṛti lists organs; economic treatises list virtues or citizens abstractly). Searches for kings, sons, sages yielded no matches.\n\n[^1]: San Hyan Kamahayanikan, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-san-hyan-kamahayanikan-2a0c19/01/translation/#p-6156f1).\n[^2]: San Hyan Kamahayanikan, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-san-hyan-kamahayanikan-2a0c19/01/translation/#p-53bcda).\n[^3]: San Hyan Kamahayanikan, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-san-hyan-kamahayanikan-2a0c19/01/translation/#p-d40865).\n[^4]: San Hyan Kamahayanikan, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-san-hyan-kamahayanikan-2a0c19/01/translation/#p-7298d4).\n[^5]: Slokantara, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-slokantara-d7a628/01/translation/#p-06703e).\n[^6]: Slokantara, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-slokantara-d7a628/01/translation/#p-c9e9c6).\n[^7]: San Hyan Tattvajnana, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-san-hyan-tattvajnana-1f29bd/01/translation/#p-9fea48).\n[^8]: San Hyan Tattvajnana, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-san-hyan-tattvajnana-1f29bd/01/translation/#p-62aca4).\n[^9]: San Hyan Tattvajnana, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-san-hyan-tattvajnana-1f29bd/01/translation/#p-f94448).",
